        <h3><a href='http://tizianoluccarelli.posterous.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Tiziano Luccarelli</a> <span class="date">Dec 5th, 2010</span></h3>
        <p>Hi there,<br />
I am from Italy and I love all the comments here.</p>
<p>@ solveig: every word you wrote is real.</p>
<p>@ American Abroad: yes, caffé latte and cappuccino are usually for breakfast and a lot of restaurant&#8217;s tenders will give you a smile ordering it after lunch or dinner. But you will have your drink, anyway. Only caffé is for after lunch/dinner, every waiter will ask you if you wish caffé at the end of your meal.</p>
<p>Hi everybody, enjoy caffé, milk and everything you wish. There&#8217;s not orthodoxy.</p>
