<li class="comment" id="comment-52723">
    <div class="authorpic">
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/ad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536?s=80' class='avatar avatar-80 photo avatar-default' height='80' width='80' /> 
	</div>
    <div class="entry">

        <h3>rhyme <span class="date">Aug 28th, 2007</span></h3>
        <p>In Australia, what you call the Americano would usually just be called a &#8220;black coffee&#8221; or sometimes, a &#8220;long black&#8221;.  The plain espresso is sometimes called a &#8220;short black&#8221;, thought that is going out of fashion these days.  A &#8220;flat white&#8221; may be what you&#8217;ve described, or it might be the Americano with a dash of cold milk added.</p>
<p>I asked for a cafe latte in Italy once.  The barista asked &#8220;cappuccino?&#8221;  I said &#8220;no, latte&#8221;.  I was given a cup of steamed milk. (Milk translates as latte).</p>
		<div class="actions">
			<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2007/08/20/an-illustrated-coffee-guide/?replytocom=52723#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-52723", "52723", "respond", "77")'>Reply</a></span>		</div>
        

