<li class="comment" id="comment-52725">
    <div class="authorpic">
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/0f8944687610f42f9191fac76f29c21a?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=R' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> 
	</div>
    <div class="entry">

        <h3>Jeena <span class="date">Aug 28th, 2007</span></h3>
        <p>Great job. Just a little note.  [kap-oo-chee-noh] is not so correct. The right pronouncation is [kapp-oo-cchee-noh]. Single or double consonants make big differences in Italian words. The same is for most of the other words in your diagram: [e-spres-oh] =&gt; [e-spress-oh] and so on.</p>
<p>Bye!</p>
		<div class="actions">
