<li class="comment" id="comment-52757">
    <div class="authorpic">
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/2903a3919090bf8ff02adc921fa47405?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=R' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> 
	</div>
    <div class="entry">

        <h3>Satin <span class="date">Aug 29th, 2007</span></h3>
        <p>Macchiato means stained.  You &#8220;stain&#8221; the black coffee with white milk.  A macchia is a stain and a smacchia is a stain remover.</p>
<p>Most orders in Italy are simple.  Caffe&#8217; (espresso), Ristretto (short espresso), Lungo (a longer espresso), Caffe&#8217; macchiato (caldo or fresco), Cappuccino, and Caffe Latte.</p>
<p>However, the very best of all is Caffe&#8217; correto or coffee &#8216;corrected&#8217; with your favorite shot of liquor.</p>
<p>It is all getting a little exagerrated outside of la bella Italia.  We can only hope that soccor/football will not move in the same direction.</p>
		<div class="actions">
			<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2007/08/20/an-illustrated-coffee-guide/?replytocom=52757#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-52757", "52757", "respond", "77")'>Reply</a></span>		</div>
        

