        <h3>snarkychef <span class="date">Aug 29th, 2007</span></h3>
        <p>I love this.  And I&#8217;d buy it on a shirt for my husband if you decide to make one available.</p>
<p>Gryndyl:  Yes, the best mocha&#8217;s use melted chocolate, but syrup is worse than powdered chocolate.  If you prepare the powdered chocolate correctly, there is no grittiness; while most syrups available these days become bitter when added to a hot liquid.  I usually have chocolate ganache on hand&#8230; just melt and add.</p>
		<div class="actions">
			<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2007/08/20/an-illustrated-coffee-guide/?replytocom=52765#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-52765", "52765", "respond", "77")'>Reply</a></span>		</div>
        

