        <h3>ariosto <span class="date">Aug 30th, 2007</span></h3>
        <p>a hah ah ah ah a ha<br />
&#8220;Caffè Latte&#8221; is note a &#8220;trademark&#8221; but only coffee=caffè + milk=latte. If you ask in Italy a &#8220;Latte&#8221;, they give you a simple cup of milk&#8230;<br />
Also a big error is only one size of cup: espresso need a little one, cappuccino a bigger one, and a &#8220;flat white&#8221;(i think &#8220;latte macchiato&#8221;) surely a glass made of glass tall and tight. The mug don&#8217;t exist in Italy bar (sure for tea or at home).<br />
I like the illustration, but i&#8217;ll never use the instructions to made something about coffee!!</p>
