<li class="comment" id="comment-52784">
    <div class="authorpic">
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/ad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536?s=80' class='avatar avatar-80 photo avatar-default' height='80' width='80' /> 
	</div>
    <div class="entry">

        <h3>Marco <span class="date">Aug 30th, 2007</span></h3>
        <p>americans shouldn&#8217;t make italian coffe-related things up.</p>
<p>&#8220;caffé macchiato&#8221; has not &#8220;milk foam&#8221; but a dab of milk. you can have it &#8220;macchiato caldo&#8221; (hot milk) or &#8220;macchiato freddo&#8221; (cold/just not hot milk).</p>
<p>cappuccino is not made of &#8220;steamed milk&#8221; and &#8220;milk foam&#8221; like two separate ingredients. you steam the milk, it makes some foam.</p>
<p>and there are no country to country variants. there&#8217;s a right way and a wrong way. you might like the wrong way better but that doesn&#8217;t make it suddenly &#8220;correct&#8221;.</p>
		<div class="actions">
			<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2007/08/20/an-illustrated-coffee-guide/?replytocom=52784#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-52784", "52784", "respond", "77")'>Reply</a></span>		</div>
        

