        <h3><a href='http://eduo.info/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>eduo</a> <span class="date">Aug 30th, 2007</span></h3>
        <p>Marco: You come off a little arrogant, don&#8217;t you think? One would assume Italy invented coffee.</p>
<p>Different countries have different variants and, even though the names were &#8220;borrowed&#8221; from the italian variants you should be mature enough to understand they stopped being direct and literal references to them.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s been made clear there are different ways of doing it and Italy being the most famous doesn&#8217;t mean it&#8217;s the only or best, just the one with the best marketing.</p>
<p>I lived in Mexico and I don&#8217;t make a fuss when someone in the U.S. talks about their version of &#8220;Tacos&#8221;.</p>
<p>Learn to be tolerant. The world assumes you&#8217;re an arrogant lamer otherwise. You have a preference but you don&#8217;t own the absolute truth. Your preference is, by definition, subjective.</p>
		<div class="actions">
			<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2007/08/20/an-illustrated-coffee-guide/?replytocom=52789#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-52789", "52789", "respond", "77")'>Reply</a></span>		</div>
        

