	</div>
    <div class="entry">

        <h3>Major D <span class="date">Aug 30th, 2007</span></h3>
        <p>Love the diagrams.  Very helpful.  But,</p>
<p>&gt; Espresso is prepared by forcing hot water through finely ground<br />
&gt; dark-roast coffee beans.</p>
<p>Steam, live steam, not hot water.  That&#8217;s why espresso machines operate under pressure and give that nice hissssssing sound.</p>
<p>If you put hot water through coffee grounds you get good ol&#8217; American coffee.</p>
		<div class="actions">
