    <div class="entry">

        <h3>Anonymous <span class="date">Aug 30th, 2007</span></h3>
        <p>&#8220;Espresso is prepared by forcing hot water through finely ground dark-roast coffee beans.&#8221;</p>
<p>Actually the best tasting espresso is made with medium roast beans. Check your sources&#8230;</p>
<p>From Wikipedia :</p>
<p>&#8220;A common misconception about espresso is that it is a specific bean or roast level. Any bean or roasting level can be used to produce authentic espresso. While some major North American chains push dark roasts as their espresso roasts, some of the winning blends used in the World Barista Championship have been what is classified as a medium or &#8220;City&#8221; or &#8220;Full City&#8221; roast, with little or no visible surface oil on the beans.&#8221;</p>
		<div class="actions">
			<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2007/08/20/an-illustrated-coffee-guide/?replytocom=52812#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-52812", "52812", "respond", "77")'>Reply</a></span>		</div>
        

    </div>
 
</li>

