<li class="comment" id="comment-53151">
    <div class="authorpic">
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/0f1152c7f1388a6f368540a049c006f3?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=R' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> 
	</div>
    <div class="entry">

        <h3>Morgan <span class="date">Oct 5th, 2007</span></h3>
        <p>re- Flat White,</p>
<p>This is made using an over-extracted espresso as a base, not just a shot of espresso, ie similar to an Americano but without being so extremely over-extracted, more like 2 shots worth of water thru one basket of grinds.</p>
<p>(over-extracted = so much water forced thru one shot in order to weaken the coffee)</p>
		<div class="actions">
			<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2007/08/20/an-illustrated-coffee-guide/?replytocom=53151#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-53151", "53151", "respond", "77")'>Reply</a></span>		</div>
        

    </div>
 
