	</div>
    <div class="entry">

        <h3>mgm <span class="date">Jun 9th, 2008</span></h3>
        <p>I haven&#8217;t seen anyone address the questions regarding cafe&#8217; au lait/misto. Misto is Starbucks&#8217; term for cafe&#8217; au lait, which, in the U.S., at least, is half regular (American) coffee and half steamed milk. I first fell in love with this drink in Paris, at an outdoor cafe, where they came to my table with two pots, one full of coffee, the other of hot milk. They poured both simultaneously into a large round cup. Delicious!!</p>
		<div class="actions">
			<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2007/08/20/an-illustrated-coffee-guide/?replytocom=53582#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-53582", "53582", "respond", "77")'>Reply</a></span>		</div>
        

