<li class="comment" id="comment-54021">
    <div class="authorpic">
		<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/df622e849dc913f6275f656a15730fdc?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=R' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> 
	</div>
    <div class="entry">

        <h3>kailing <span class="date">Apr 22nd, 2009</span></h3>
        <p>Also in Spain there is something deliciuos for summer: Coffee on the Rocks (Cafe con Hielo-Coffee with Ice). Cold coffee is usually cold american coffee brewed long ago and let it cool, losing the aroma. For a summer &#8220;delight&#8221;:<br />
1) Ask for a expresso or a bouble expresso<br />
2) and a glass with ice cubes<br />
3) (for those who add sugar [OMG!]: add the sugar to the hot expresso and stirr)<br />
4) Pour the coffee on the glass with ice and stirr.</p>
<p>Indulge yourself with all the aroma of a cold expresso.</p>
		<div class="actions">
			<span class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2007/08/20/an-illustrated-coffee-guide/?replytocom=54021#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-54021", "54021", "respond", "77")'>Reply</a></span>		</div>
        

